# Styling Guidelines

All styles in Anori use SCSS. Follow these guidelines for consistency and maintainability.

## File Organization

* Each component should have its own `.scss` file alongside the component file.
* Base styles are defined in `src/components/base.scss` (global resets, CSS variables).
* Shared utilities are in `src/components/utils.scss` (mixins, variables).

## Module System

Always use `@use` instead of `@import`:

```scss
@use "@anori/components/utils.scss" as utils;
@use "@anori/components/base.scss";
```

## CSS Variables & Theming

Theme variables are defined in `:root` in `base.scss`:

* Colors: `--accent`, `--accent-subtle`, `--background`, `--background-lighter`, `--text`, `--text-hsl`, `--text-subtle-1`, `--text-subtle-2`, `--text-disabled`, `--icon-color`, `--error-color`
* Widget sizing: `--widget-box-size`, `--widget-box-size-px`, `--widget-box-percent` (available on folder root elements)

Use HSL-based colors with opacity: `hsla(var(--text-hsl) / 0.1)` for semi-transparent colors.

## Naming Conventions

Use BEM-like naming: `.ComponentName` for root class, `.ComponentName-modifier` for variants.

Examples: `.Button`, `.Button-size-compact`, `.Button-loading`, `.Modal-backdrop`

### Child Elements

Child element classes use kebab-case and are nested within the component root:

```scss
.Modal {
    padding: 24px;

    .modal-header {
        display: flex;
        gap: 16px;

        .close-button {
            border: none;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
    }
}
```

For major child components that might be reused or need clear identification, use full component prefix: `.ComponentName-childName` (e.g., `.WidgetExpandArea-content`, `.WidgetExpandArea-backdrop`).

* **Nesting depth**: Keep nesting to 2-3 levels maximum. If deeper nesting is needed, consider extracting to a separate class or component.

## Responsive Design Mixins

Use mixins from `utils.scss` for responsive/device-specific styles:

```scss
@use "@anori/components/utils.scss" as utils;

.foo {
    padding: 2rem;
    
    @include utils.compact { 
        padding: 1rem;
    }
    
    @include utils.hover {
        background: var(--background-lighter);
    }
    
    @include utils.touch {
        padding: 1.5rem;
    }
    
    @include utils.android {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
    
    @include utils.rtl {
        padding-left: 0;
        padding-right: 1rem;
    }
}
```

* `utils.compact` — styles for compact mode
* `utils.hover` — hover styles only on non-touch devices (preferred over `:hover`)
* `utils.touch` — styles for touch devices
* `utils.android` — Android-specific styles
* `utils.rtl` — RTL language support

## Units & Sizing

* Prefer `rem` for typography and spacing (scalable, accessible).
* Use `px` for precise values (borders, scrollbars, fixed dimensions).
* Use CSS variables for dynamic sizing.
* Use `100dvh`/`100dvw` instead of `100vh`/`100vw` for viewport units (handles mobile browser UI).

Common spacing values: `0.5rem`, `0.75rem`, `1rem`, `1.5rem`, `2rem`, `24px`.

Common border-radius values: `8px`, `12px`, `24px`, `36px`.

## Layout Patterns

* Use Flexbox for layouts (`display: flex`, `flex-direction: column/row`).
* Use `gap` property for spacing between flex items.
* Prefer semantic HTML and CSS Grid only when flexbox is insufficient.

## Scrollbars

* Use `<ScrollArea />` component instead of native `overflow: scroll`.
* Custom scrollbar styling is handled via `scroll-mixin` and `scroll-mixin-darker` in `utils.scss` if needed.

## Color Usage Patterns

* Text hierarchy: `var(--text)` → `var(--text-subtle-1)` → `var(--text-subtle-2)` → `var(--text-disabled)`
* Backgrounds: `var(--background)` → `var(--background-lighter)`
* Borders: `hsla(var(--text-hsl) / 0.1)` for subtle borders
* Icons: `var(--icon-color)` (defaults to `hsla(var(--text-hsl) / 0.4)`)

## Component-Specific Patterns

* **Modals**: `border-radius: 24px`, backdrop blur, fixed positioning with `100dvw`/`100dvh`
* **Buttons**: Transparent default, border variant with `border-radius: 24px`, use `utils.hover` mixin
* **Inputs**: `border-radius: 8px`, `var(--background-lighter)` background, `var(--accent)` focus outline
* **Widget cards**: `border-radius: 12px`, `var(--background-lighter)` background, padding via `.with-padding` modifier

## Accessibility & Touch

* Use `user-select: none` for interactive elements that shouldn't be selectable.
* Always use `utils.hover` mixin instead of `:hover` to avoid hover styles on touch devices.